snippet.textDisplay: Ike Taylor is still my guy even now.  Never the best in the league, but always reliable.  I remember a game his last couple years in Pittsburgh where the announcers kept talking about him struggling against the other teams #1 guy, but he would just calmly line right back up again.  No complaining, no nothing, then he ended up breaking up a touchdown pass and ending the drive.  With how bad the secondary got, I kept telling myself, “man, if Ike Taylor were still here, this wouldn't be happening...”
